ED_Title: 2001–2010: Decade to Roll Back Malaria in Developing Countries, Particularly in Africa
ED_DecisionText: At its 102nd plenary meeting, on 8 September 2022, the General Assembly decided to defer consideration of the item entitled “2001–2010: Decade to Roll Back Malaria in Developing Countries, Particularly in Africa” and to include it in the draft agenda of its seventy-seventh session.
ED_Disclaimer: The final text of this decision will be contained in document A/76/49 (Vol. III) after editorial review.
